= render 'breadcrumbs'

%h1
  Import Clients
%p
  Use this form to upload a CSV of set-aside preference forms.
  The file must have the following headers, in the following order:

%ul
  - @upload.parsed_expected_header.each do |header|
    %li= header

%p
  Any newly imported clients will be made available for matching.
  Existing clients that appear in the upload will be updated with any new information
  in the file, but, will not be made available for matching if they are currently
  ineligible.

= simple_form_for @upload, url: imported_clients_path, method: :post do |f|
  = f.error_notification
  .form-inputs
    = f.input :file, as: :file, label: false
  .form-actions
    = f.button :submit, value: 'Upload CSV'
